Xan out <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdrinal28133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raytheonhcn>RaytheonHCN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Raper of Egos</span><br>  Posts: 583<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/02 8:13:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=22>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.highcouncil.net/legoray1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: You 7</span><hr size=1> In the week it took me to come to my final decision about what I was going to do, I weighed the pros and cons.  One of the cons was that some muckraker would feel the need to come here and air our business to the world.  Fine.  This was the hardest decision I have ever made in this game, and for you to insinuate that it was made because of greed is not only completely untrue, but it is insulting as well.  Nothing I have EVER done in my EQ tenure has been motivated by greed.  <br>
<br>
My decision to move on was motivated by the desire to do and see things in game that I personally felt a family/casual style guild like HCoN would not see for a long time, if ever.  This is not to say that HCoN's structure is bad, just that a few of us were beginning to outgrow it.  HCoN is a GREAT group of people, all of whom I have been proud to say have stretched the limits on what a smaller guild can accomplish.  I am proud of each and every member of HCoN and what they have helped the guild become. As the leaders, we very easily could have changed HCoN to be the type of guild we wanted it to be in the end.  We could have changed the rules and selectively recruited to get the guild to the point that we could start taking down anything we wanted at a moment's notice.  This we could have done, but we would have alienated 80% of the membership in doing so.  So what's better; changing the guild from what made it great and what most of the guild was happy with, or having the few that wanted change move on and seek thier own happiness?  People have said that we failed as leaders to move the guild in the direction we wanted.  Maybe so, but to me part of the responsibility of leadership is knowing when you become a detriment, and when its time to step down.  I felt it was the right time.  If I was wrong, thats something I'm going to have to live with.<br>
<br>
Sure, we could have given more warning, and worked better to ensure a smoother transfer of leadership, and for that I am sorry.  Every one of my former guildmates knows I still support them and will help them in ways I am not going to discuss here.  I have complete faith that those who chose to remain behind will do a superb job of picking up the reins and will continue to lead HCoN to greatness. <br>
<br>
The bottom line for me was that no matter what words the pixels are arranged into above my character's head, I still consider the friendships I have made in HCoN and with people in other guilds to be sacrosanct.  I would do anything for any last one of them, and they all know it.  Some of them are still upset with me, and that tears me up, but I hope they all know that I still consider then all friends, even if they do not consider me one anymore.<br>
<br>
This was alot more than I was going to post here,  but when i start rambling...  <br>
<br>
To sum up: <br>
<br>
To HCoN members.  You know what I have said, and you know why I chose what I chose.  I am sorry if it caused strife, but I know in my heart that you are all strong enough to pick up where we left off and continue on strong.  It was an unbeliveably painful decision to make over a game, and increasingly harder because we dissapointed friends.  Good luck friends, I am only a tell away if you need me.<br>
<br>
To everyone else:  M.Y.O.F.B.<br>
<br>
