Higar, I have no doubt that HCoN has very few limits when they decide to gather together for a common purpose.   I have personally been amazed at some of the things we have done.  However, the constant exploration of new higher-level content and encounters requires time, numbers, effort, motivation, sacrifice and practice.  HCoN has exhibited every one of those traits, but very rarely at the same time. This is not a fault, but a natural result of a generally open, friendly casual guild.  Your obervation that "when we get in the mood, shit dies" (which, by the way as of last week graces all of HCoN's web pages and message boards typed in an elvish font in the top banner) is exactly descriptive of HCoN.  Some of us were just in the mood more than others, or at different times than most others.   <p><center>
